README file for XMPP MTP for JADE, Version $Name: JADE-3_3 $

INTRODUCTION
============

This file contains a XMPP MTP for JADE.
Available at http://........


LICENSE
=======
See file COPYING


SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
===================

This MTP requires JADE, smack and crimson libraries.

SAMCK Homepage: http://www.jivesoftware.org/smack/
CRIMSON Homepage: http://xml.apache.org/crimson/

INSTALLATION
============

This MTP is contained into a separate JAR file, named xmpp.jar; in
order to be used, the xmpp.jar file must be added to the CLASSPATH
environment variable.


USING THE NEW MTP
=================

Installing from the binary distribution of JADE
-----------------------------------------------

In the binary distribution, JADE is contained into three JAR files:

  - jade.jar (Basic JADE runtime system)
  - jadeTools.jar (JADE graphical tools)
  - iiop.jar (Basic IIOP MTP)
  - http.jar (Basic HTTP MTP)

If you want to use the XMPP MTP, you have to include in your
CLASSPATH the following files:

  - jade.jar (Basic JADE runtime system)
  - xmpp.jar (XMPP MTP)
  - crimson.jar (XML Parser)


Run the MTPs from the command line
--------------------------------------

In this case the following parameter must be specified on the command line.
  -mtp jade.mtp.xmpp.MessageTransportProtocol
  -jade_mtp_xmpp_server <jabber server>
  -jade_mtp_xmpp_username <username>
  -jade_mtp_xmpp_password <password>

As an Example:

java jade.Boot -mtp jade.mtp.xmpp.MessageTransportProtocol -jade_mtp_xmpp_server  jabber.org -jade_mtp_xmpp_username jade -jade_mtp_xmpp_password secret

Supported MTP address kinds
---------------------------

The XMPP MTP supports 'xmpp://' addresses.

